title: For Sale/Trade:  PTR91 Customized Compact Battle Rifle .308 7.62 LOADED
postcontent:
I have just over 1900 invested into this rifle.

FOR SALE OR TRADE: LIKE-NEW PTR-91, heavily customized, accurized and built to be a compact battle rifle, modified to a "Congo" style, or Super-K configuration.

AMERICAN-MADE TO HK SPEC ON ORIGINAL HK MACHINERY

14.5" barrel, properly pinned and welded to just over 16". This is not an SBR per ATF's definition and is fully legal to own without extra paperwork, tax stamps, registration, etc.

Barrel re-threading and crowning was performed by Jayson Cotter at Investment Grade Firearms. He's a legend HK smith, Google him if you wish. His reputation speaks for itself.

Muzzle device is a CNC Warrior 8-port brake that drastically reduces the muzzle climb inherent to the .308 round.

Factory-welded picatinny rail for optics mounting.

Buttpad is an HK21-E machine gun wide rubber buttpad.

Inside the stock is an Enhanced Heavy DMR Buffer. Stock buffer will ship with the gun if wanted (spare parts are never a bad thing).

Trigger is a custom match trigger from Bill Springfield (another legend) doing work at 4 lbs, down from 11.5 in the stock military trigger. Makes for some very precise shots and very nice groups, also aids immensely in doling out double and triple-taps on man-sized targets.

Wraparound Hogue Grip has been installed over the Navy polymer pistol grip. It is much more comfortable against the palm. Grip has an added thumb swell to it. Really reduces the beating the hand can take when firing.

Wide German handguard, complete with light steel bipod. Legs fit flush to grooves.

Slimline battle rifle handguard.

Blue Force Gear Larry Vickers VCAS padded sling. This sling is brand new in a Kryptek Mandrake pattern. Still a little stiff in spots. The VCAS is currently standard-issue in the United States Marine Corps for a reason. It's impossible to destroy and comfy as hell. The quick-adjustable pull tab lets you looses up or tighten up in half a second. If you have experience with this sling, you already know. If not, trust me you will feel it the first time you drop it over you. Will ship installed on rifle unless specified otherwise by buyer.

Ships with eight (8) mags, manual and lock in original hardcase.

Fully, properly fluted chamber built to original HK spec on original HK tooling. Will eat ALL ammo you can feed it, steel or brass. Currently has a very low count of about 130 rounds down the pipe, from primo .308 ADI Outback hunting loads to bulk mil-spec 7.62 NATO. Have scored a hair under MOA with several loads inlcuding PPU 150 gr, MKE 7.62 NATO spec (the ZQ1 walmart stuff) and ADI Outback 168 BSPs.

I chose the HK system for this project because of its inherent reliability. It is virtually guaranteed to go bang, all you need is a round in the chamber. No pistons, no gas tubes. The fluting (when properly done as original HK barrels were) ensured cycling with even the worst battlefield pickup ammo. So, if you're looking for a fully tuned, match-grade, compact, hard-hitting, cover and barrier penetrating battle rifle, here it is.

Given the fact that it is used, albeit very slightly, I am open to an offer of 1700 cash.

I ship to FFL and FFL only. Non-negotiable. Please know your laws regarding weapons and mags where you live. No sales to ban states. I apologize for this it is just too difficult and dangerous at this time.

USPS money orders or (discreet) PayPal.

Thank you for your interest. Please do not hesitate to ask any questions or request further pics. Thank you.

Additional info: The Primary Arms 1-6x ACSS pictured in some photos is not included. Please note: I mounted it using low rings and as such removed the rear sight. It is a single philips screw, not complicated putting it back on, but it will have to be re-zeroed.

TRADE: I am also willing to trade for a Springfield M1A Scout Squad with sub-1000 round count, mags and accessories. Email me any time.
